cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with human activity analysis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning warping functions, which is a machine learning task and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions improvements in action recognition, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to learning warping functions, which can be seen as a form of neural network architecture design, falling under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
